role: dev
task: S04-T1
title: Audit and apply S02/S03 design tokens app-wide
gate: OPEN
stack_source: @incoming/requirements.md
stack: [TypeScript, React, MobX, Material UI]
requires: [UI]

objective: |
  Ensure no screen or component bypasses S02/S03 invariants. Dark theme and glass
  tokens must be the single source of truth across all app surfaces.

context:
  - S02/S03 invariants define dark palette and glass button/card/modal patterns.
  - Orphan screens or inline colors break the "command-center" consistency.

steps:
  1. List all top-level routes and layout containers; verify each uses .dark and token-based colors.
  2. Replace any remaining arbitrary hex/rgb with tokens from S02-INVARIANTS (--background, --primary, glass-*).
  3. Ensure all interactive surfaces use glass-button or glass-card variants per S03.
  4. Confirm modal-backdrop and .modal-glass are used for any overlay UI.

acceptance-criteria:
  - No hardcoded colors outside the invariant token map.
  - Every major view uses dark theme and glass components where applicable.
  - Build passes; no visual regressions on existing flows.
